{"lemma":"جَعْدٌ","slug":"جَعْدٌ","root":"ج.ع.د","root_slug":"ج-ع-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ع-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n5892"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%AF%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be curly, to be crisp, to be twisted, to be wavy; to become curly, to become crisp, to become twisted, to become wavy"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make curly or twisted, to wrinkle, crumple up"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"crispy, creasy, curly"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"stingy, closefisted"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n5892","headword_ar":"جَعْدٌ","root":"jEd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to hair, (S, A, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Crisp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twisted, and contracted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTN","text_ar":"سَبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotarosilN","text_ar":"مُسْتَرْسِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"short."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, K.) ―         -b2-  Applied to a man, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having hair such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEod","text_ar":"جَعْد"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K:) [or]"},{"kind":"page_break","n":429},{"kind":"text","text":"so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEodu Al$~aEari","text_ar":"جَعْدُ الشَّعَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, TA:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiEaAdN","text_ar":"جِعَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, Msb.) ―         -b3-  As an epithet of praise, it has two meanings; namely, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Compact in limbs, and strong in make; not flabby, nor of slack,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incongruous, make;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"big,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bulky, and compact;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 238;) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having crisp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curly, not lank, hair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because lankness is the prevalent characteristic of the hair of the Greeks and Persians; and crispness, or curliness, is the prevalent characteristic of the hair of the Arabs: but very crisp, or frizzled, or woolly, hair, like that of the Zenj and the Nubians, is disapproved. (L.) ―         -b4-  [Hence,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Generous; bountiful; munificent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, A, K;) alluding to a man's being an Arab of generous disposition, because the Arabs are characterized by crisp, or curly, hair. (A.) As did not know"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jEd","text_ar":"جعد"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense; but it occurs in many verses of the Ansár. (T, TA.) ―         -b5-  As an epithet of dispraise, it has also two meanings; namely, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Short, and incongruous in make:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTN","text_ar":"سَبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] ―         -b6-  and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Niggardly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, S, L, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEodu Alyadayoni","text_ar":"جَعْدُ اليَدَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEodu AlA^anaAmilu","text_ar":"جَعْدُ الاَنَامِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEodu AlA^aSaAbiEu","text_ar":"جَعْدُ الاَصَابِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or this signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having short fingers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEodu","text_ar":"جَعْدُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbanaAni","text_ar":"البَنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEodu Alkaf~i","text_ar":"جَعْدُ الكَفِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Har p. 96,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEodu","text_ar":"جَعْدُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljanaAni","text_ar":"الجَنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTu Alyadayoni","text_ar":"سَبْطُ اليَدَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sbTu Alyadi","text_ar":"سبطُ اليَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sbTu AlbanaAni","text_ar":"سبطُ البَنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]: (Har ubi suprà:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mean; ungenerous; base:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEodu","text_ar":"جَعْدُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqafaA","text_ar":"القَفَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ignoble, in respect of rank, quality, reputation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) ―         -b7-  A camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having much fur:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having crisp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curly, and abundant, fur."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw AljaEodi","text_ar":"اَبُو الجَعْدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"a surname of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b8-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Soft"},{"kind":"text","text":"moist earth; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaEodN","text_ar":"ثَعْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moist"},{"kind":"text","text":"earth. (K.) ―         -b9-  (assumed tropical:)  A mess of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hayos","text_ar":"حَيْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"that is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not flowing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujaE~adN","text_ar":"مُجَعَّدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, K.) IAar cites the following words of a poet, accusing a woman of foul conduct:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"↓ \n      wataxoliTu biAlmaA^oquwTi HayosFA mujaE~adFA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And she mixes thick"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hys","text_ar":"حيس"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the food prepared with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqiT","text_ar":"اَقِط"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning, she confounds men together, and does not select him who is to have intercourse with her. (L.) ―         -b10-  (assumed tropical:)  Froth, or foam,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accumulated upon the fore part of the mouth"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a camel. (S, * L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEodu All~ugaAmi","text_ar":"جَعْدُ اللُّغَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  A camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having froth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foam, accumulated upon the fore part of his mouth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * L, K. *) ―         -b11-  (assumed tropical:)  A cheek"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse, and short; not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asiyl","text_ar":"اَسِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, K.) And (assumed tropical:) A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"round"},{"kind":"text","text":"face,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with little"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miloH","text_ar":"مِلْح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beauty"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K, TA,) or, as in some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laHom","text_ar":"لَحْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flesh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadamN jaEodapN","text_ar":"قَدَمٌ جَعْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A short foot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA;) characteristic of low origin. (TA.) ―         -b12-  It is also applied, in the manner of an intensive epithet, to the plant called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sil~iyaAn","text_ar":"صِلِّيَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in like manner, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", to the plant called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buhomaY","text_ar":"بُهْمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN jaEodapN","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ جَعْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-camel compact in make, and strong."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","TA","L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}